<TEXT>
following is the text of iraqi president 
saddam husseins open letter to president bush broadcast by the 
iraqi media in arabic and translated by the associated press 
in the name of god the almighty the compassionate 
an open letter to the president of the united states 
i have become aware of your latest statements and heated 
comments before the staff of the american defense ministry that 
reflected your intention in pursuing a policy harmful to iraq a 
policy of occupation that humiliates the sacred shrine and lands of 
the arabs and moslems in hijaz and najd 
i will not hesitate mr president to tell you that while i 
read your words that reflected clearly your mockery and disregard 
for the arab mentality and national and official arab sentiment 
your shallowness became so apparent i had thought you were more 
farsighted than that and i cannot but admit that my conviction in 
the just policy chosen by the iraqi people which i serve and lead 
has increased and so has increased my conviction in the 
righteousness of every patriotic arab and moslem who supports the 
path of holy war against the invading forces 
you have tried you as a president of a superpower along 
with your small agents to brand saddam hussein a liar after 
failing to stab him in other ways you all whose files are 
thickest in this respect 
you and your business partners in the region and your agents 
have said that saddam hussein promised egyptian president hosni 
mubarak that he would not do this or that yet he did although you 
are fully aware that it is beyond your wildest dream that saddam 
hussein should lie because he who lies will undoubtedly lose the 
ability of persuasion lose the drive for determination and lose 
the basic requirements for confidence 
what you the policymakers in the united states and your 
small agents in the region hate above all is the veracity of men 
and the most hated among these men is saddam hussein because his 
sincerity toward principles toward himself his people and his 
country make of him a true servant and leader of the people not a 
servant for the foreigner you consider those liars in the region 
your trusted friends although you are fully aware who is the liar 
and who are the liars in the region 
the western public opinion even the american public opinion 
will be on the side of righteousness so that even when the 
confrontation intensifies and the speeches become abundant your 
face and that of your mutilated allies will be unveiled and the 
americans will tell you we have unified america with blood so why 
are you acting against the unity of the people of iraq who were 
split by colonialism and why are you falling in the laps of those 
retarded opportunists 
they will ask you where are these legitimate interests that 
are threatened by iraq when they realize that iraq welcomes the 
legitimate interests the anger of the american people will rise 
and it is then that your downfall will come and the defeat will be 
inevitable for the forces that you had massed and hoped to use to 
terrorize the arab nation this great nation from which emerged the 
prophets and holy books 
you have lied mr us president to your people when you 
told them that you were massing troops to protect american 
