<TEXT>
gov l douglas wilder told virginians on 
thursday night he will freeze state employee salaries cut state 
spending by 375 million and consider eliminating some agencies to 
cope with budget woes 
some layoffs and office closings will result from the proposals 
to deal with a projected 14 billion shortfall in the states 26 
billion 19901992 budget the governor said in a statewide 
televised address 
my plan is tough but fair wilder said this plan requires 
government to be more efficient and effective in its use of scarce 
resources 
wilder said he would not recommend any increase in taxes would 
not reduce direct aid payments to the poor and medically needy 
would maintain public safety funding and would keep a 200 million 
budget reserve for emergencies 
the major points of his plan included 
reducing state agency budgets by nearly 375 million over the 
next two years 
every agency of state government including colleges and 
universities direct service agencies administrative agencies 
and yes even the office of the governor will reduce 
expenditures he said 
wilder said some employees will be laid off some field offices 
will be closed and some agencies and programs will be eliminated 
eliminate state funding for private museums foundations and 
attractions these projects cost 11 million in the current 
twoyear budget he said their funding will be reduced this fiscal 
year and recommended for elimination next fiscal year wilder said 
continue a moratorium on state construction for all but the 
most essential projects about 300 million in projected lottery 
profits over the next two years will go to operating expenses 
instead of building construction 
withhold 2 percent salary increases that state employees were 
to have received in december saving more than 145 million 
reduce state aid to localities which makes up more than half 
the states budget wilder did not specify how much aid would be 
reduced 
wilder said he will ask the general assembly in january to 
eliminate the department of world trade and possibly the department 
of volunteerism the council on the status of women and the council 
on indians 
the governor also said he will look into consolidating 
childrens services handled by several state agencies 
he said he would study cutting the use of stateowned vehicles 
cutting the number of field offices in the department of motor 
vehicles and providing an early retirement program to reduce the 
state work force 
in a 14minute televised response republicans said the governor 
had borrowed many of their ideas for budget cutting but still did 
not go far enough 
