japanese officials today began investigating 
reports that us jet fighters buzzed japanese pleasure boats as 
imaginary targets during training flights 
us military officials said navy aircraft were training in the 
area wednesday where two yachts were buzzed by jet fighters 
the us officials speaking on condition of anonymity would 
not give any further details about the incidents in which a man 
was injured after a lowflying fighter buzzed his yacht 
japans maritime safety agency has received reports from local 
fishermen and boat captains of similar incidents occurring in the 
same area during the last two months agency spokesman naoki maeda 
said 
the presence of the us armed forces in japan under a mutual 
security pact is still a sensitive topic and reports of accidents 
involving us military personnel receive wide publicity 
he quoted one person as saying that earlier this month two jets 
with us military marks suddenly flew down very low as if they had 
been aiming at yachts near oshima an island 70 miles south of 
tokyo 
japanese newspapers quoting us military sources said the jets 
involved in wednesdays incidents were fa18 fighters attached to 
the aircraft carrier midway 
kyodo news service reported that japanese officials believed the 
fighters were using the pleasure craft as imaginary enemy targets 
