death squads from haiti to el salvador 
in the process they became skeptical of their own government 
everything is really interconnected said amy voege a 
23yearold junior at central michigan university in mount 
pleasant mich 
the people who are fleeing their countries are fleeing because 
of human rights abuses there or fleeing because of war there 
she said but those human rights abuses and those wars are really 
supported by the united states government 
they will take back memories of those they helped among them 
was a honduran soldier who said he was beaten for refusing to 
