<TEXT>
tens of thousands of pakistanis 
reeling from 20 turbulent months of democracy streamed today to 
the grave of gen mohammad zia ulhaqs to pay tribute to the 
fallen dictator on the second anniversary of his death 
mourners traveled by foot cart and bus to the giant faisal 
mosque to offer prayers for zia who died aug 17 1988 in a 
mysterious plane crash all 37 people aboard including several top 
generals and us ambassador arnold raphel were killed 
zias son ijaz ulhaq placed wreaths at the graves of the 
other generals today and then led a huge procession to the faisal 
mosque from the neighboring city of rawalpindi the headquarters of 
the army that has ruled pakistan for more than half of its 43year 
history 
mourners planned to offer prayers for zia later today to mark 
the time his plane crashed in a desert in eastern punjab province 
ijaz was to offer a tribute using the occasion to launch his own 
political career 
zias death anniversary comes less than two weeks after former 
prime minister benazir bhuttos government was dismissed on charges 
of corruption nepotism and ineptitude 
ms bhutto whose father was overthrown by zia in 1977 claims a 
similar coup was staged against her but camouflaged by the 
constitution 
her father zulfikar ali bhutto was hanged in 1979 on charges 
of conspiring the murder a political enemy who was never killed 
she blames zia 
while in power ms bhutto proclaimed her father a martyr for 
democracy ijaz says his father was a martyr for islam 
sixfoot posters of the former military ruler line the wide 
boulevards of the capital giant banners proclaiming zia a martyr 
flutter in the warm summer breeze 
with the future of democracy uncertain many pakistanis are 
fondly remembering zia as a humble compassionate man and 
reminiscing about military rule 
hundreds of people make the pilgrimage to zias grave daily 
ijaz a 38yearold banker on the verge of running for office 
insists that his father was a good model for a candidate 
benazir bhuttos father was a civilian dictator and she came 
to power why cant the son of zia ulhaq asked ijaz 
elections are scheduled for oct 24 but speculation is rife 
that they will be postponed and that another round of military rule 
is inevitable 
a fourfoot framed picture of the former dictator dominates 
ijazs living room propped up at its side is a smaller picture of 
zia one hand on his heart in front of the white house with former 
president reagan striking a similar pose 
zias hercules c130 had been in the air less than five minutes 
when it weaved out of control and nosedived into the ground 
according to witnesses 
a technical report charged sabotage but a criminal 
investigation was never pursued ms bhuttos government made a 
weak attempt at probing the crash and the us government waited a 
year before sending investigators 
ijaz blames alzulfikar a group led by ms bhuttos brother 
murtaza it hijacked a plane in the mid1980s and zia had said 
they were behind several failed assassination attempts 
ijaz also claims president ghulam ishaq khan the army and the 
united states staged a coverup 
