<TEXT>
the trial of 40 soldiers and 
civilians accused in the 1983 murder of president corazon aquinos 
husband ended today but a verdict could take another year a court 
official said 
former sen benigno aquino was assassinated aug 21 1983 as he 
stepped from a plane at the manila airport he was returning from 
selfimposed exile in the united states to lead the opposition 
against the late president ferdinand marcos 
marcos alleged that aquino was killed by a communist assassin 
rolando galman who soldiers shot dead on the tarmac prosecutors 
argued galman was part of a military conspiracy and that a soldier 
actually killed aquino 
prosecutors today asked the court to render a guilty verdict 
with the qualifying circumstances of evident premeditation and 
treachery and taking advantage of their government positions 
aquinos slaying sparked massive protests that swept his widow 
to the presidency in february 1986 after a people power revolt 
ousted marcos and drove him to exile in the united states marcos 
died in hawaii in september 1989 
under mrs aquinos administration the supreme court overturned 
a december 1985 acquittal of former chief of staff fabian ver 24 
soldiers and one civilian after the court found evidence that 
marcos engineered the decision ver fled the country during the 
1986 uprising 
in april 1987 government prosecutors indicted 40 people for the 
murder of aquino and galman the case was filed with the 
sandiganbayan court which tries state employees charged with civil 
and criminal suits 
the 40 included ver two generals 33 soldiers and four 
civilians including former tourism minister jose aspiras now a 
member of the house of representatives who was an alleged 
accomplice 
also charged as accomplices were former information minister 
gregorio cendana and former air and former transport minister jesus 
singson 
the 3yearlong trial culminated today after defense lawyers 
and prosecutors submitted summaries of their arguments to the 
threemember court 
clerk of court dolores balajadia said that under philippine law 
the panel of judges has up to one year to make a final ruling 
there are no juries in the philippines where a verdict is the 
responsibility of judges 
during the trial the court saw photographs tape recordings and 
video footage of the seconds before and after aquino slumped dead 
on the tarmac with a single bullet wound in the back of the head 
it also heard the testimony of 51 defense and 79 prosecution 
witnesses including four who claimed they saw a soldier kill 
aquino 
</TEXT>
