a century after the prince of wales 
tailor invented the tailless dinner jacket saratoga springs and 
tuxedo park are rolling up the sleeves of their pleatedfront 
shirts over which town introduced the tux to america 
ed hotaling a parttime columnist for the saratogian stirred 
things up by suggesting that tuxedos be renamed saratogas he 
contends the english creation made its debut in his summer resort 
hometown in upstate new york in the late 1880s 
the exclusive community of tuxedo park 40 miles northwest of 
new york city says the origin is in its name 
tuxedo park mayor cornelius jj madera jr said hotalings 
claim like saratogas famous racetrack smells of horses 
theyre spending too much time in the barns he said 
hotaling who began his campaign nine months ago wrote 
wednesday of a day when all waiters will look down at you in 
their saratogas invitations to parties will note the required 
mens wear in tiny letters saratoga 
hotaling claimed the semiformal evening jacket was first worn to 
a ball in saratoga springs grand union hotel by local playboy e 
berry wall he cites as his source the social historian george 
waller author of saratoga saga of an impious era 
but tuxedo park historian albert f winslow said a more likely 
story is that one of tuxedo parks founders james brown potter 
brought the tuxedo back from england 
the jacket was later picked up by griswold lorillard son of one 
of the founders of tuxedo park who wore a formal jacket with the 
tails cut off to a ball in 1886 winslow said 
you get a couple of department stores selling saratogas 
youll get a change growled hotaling who is also a producer for 
abc news in washington 
but its unlikely the dinner jacket will undergo a name change 
anytime soon 
i just couldnt imagine it happening when a names so 
entrenched in peoples minds said nick valentine owner of 
broadway tailors in newburgh if you say tuxedo you mean formal 
wear 
