the departments office of professional responsibility is 
conducting the investigation into the case of andrija artukovic 
the los angeles times quoted unidentified sources as saying 
one official familiar with the probe said there was no evidence 
artukovic was falsely convicted of ordering the deaths of hundreds 
of serbs jews and gypsies during world war ii the newspaper said 
artukovic served as a cabinet minister in a nazi puppet 
government in wartime croatia that executed thousands he emigrated 
to the united states in 1948 under an alias and resided in seal 
beach before he was identified and extradited to yugoslavia in 
1986 two years later he died at age 88 in a yugoslav prison 
