seven people have been arrested in connection 
with the alleged delivery of a poison gas plant to iraq several 
years ago a west german prosecutor said today 
the prosecutor friedrich hoffmann in darmstadt said that among 
those arrested was a man he identified only as al kadhi an iraqi 
specialist employed by the west german foreign intelligence service 
hoffmann said the arrests which came after several years of 
investigation took so long because evidence was needed to prove 
that the plant allegedly delivered to iraq was constructed to 
produce poison gas 
the arrests were based on violation of west german export laws 
which limit and in many cases ban the sale or delivery of weapons 
of destruction to areas of conflict such as the middle east 
hoffmann said 
he said the plant produced mustard gas among other deadly 
chemical agents 
among those arrested were employees of the pilot plant company 
in dreieich 12 miles south of frankfurt workers in the export 
section of the preussag company in hanover and from the walter 
engineering trading company in hamburg hoffmann said 
