<TEXT>
ambassadors of the five permanent members 
of the security council held an unprecedented joint meeting with 
senior military aides friday to discuss an expanded un military 
role in the persian gulf crisis 
the purpose of this gathering was to exchange information on 
the naval activities in the gulf and in the area french 
ambassador pierre louis blanc told reporters after the meeting at 
the french mission 
the session was attended by un envoys of the united states 
britain china france and the soviet union and by military 
advisers of the five governments together known as the security 
councils military staff committee 
the committee was created 44 years ago when the united nations 
was new but has been inactive meeting on a perfunctory basis two 
times a month 
diplomats emphasized that friday was no ordinary meeting it 
included senior us british and french officers a senior soviet 
official was unable to attend and the level of the chinese military 
was not known 
blanc said consultations were informal and further meetings 
could follow if the need arises 
no immediate indication surfaced that the five were moving to 
form a joint un military command in the gulf or to fly the un 
flag but western observers said the five had moved with 
extraordinary speed to discuss coordination for the first time and 
reactivate a un military role 
we wont have a un army tomorrow one said but we could 
have exchange of information and coordination letting each other 
know about rules of engagement and that is quite significant 
by un standards that is whirlwind progress 
the observers spoke on condition of anonymity 
under the un charter the military staff committee is charged 
with coordinating all un military actions of an enforcement 
nature excluding peacekeeping 
it is intended to organize and command joint military 
operations which never have come into existence the last time the 
un flag was flown in a un enforcement operation was during the 
195053 korean war 
that war was not strictly a un operation however and was 
handed over to the united states 
moscow has been pressing for an expanded un peacekeeping role 
and for revival of the un military staff committee foreign 
