drastic cutbacks if the budget impasse isnt broken by oct 1 at 
that time the government would implement the grammrudman 
deficitreduction law he said 
if grammrudman goes into effect the faa would have to slash 
spending about 32 percent busey said while speaking at the atlanta 
aero club 
that means i will have to begin furloughing members of the 
work force to the extent that we will have approximately 30 percent 
of our work force on furlough on any given day he said that 
will cause a corresponding reduction in our ability to control air 
traffic between 25 and 35 percent 
the administrator said he notified his work force of about 
50000 on monday about the prospect of furloughs each worker would 
have to take off up to 2 normal working days each twoweek pay 
period 
memos sent this week by the office of personnel management are 
telling the nations 24 million federal workers they could face up 
to 22 days off without pay in the fiscal year that begins oct 1 
or about one day in each twoweek pay period 
busey said the furloughs would apply across the board to air 
traffic controllers maintenance inspectors equipment specialists 
and security officials 
i dont know how to prioritize between those 
responsibilities he said therefore an acrosstheboard 
furlough mechanism is the only way i know how to manage 
he said he intends to discuss the contingency plans next week 
with the air transport association a trade group that represents 
virtually all us airlines 
