<TEXT>
clothing colors and table manners can make or 
break business executives image consultants said here at their 
annual trade show 
we have been programmed by television to deliver a message in 
30 seconds said marily mondejar founder and executive director 
of image industry council international a trade organization for 
consultants who teach businesses how to polish their images 
in the first five seconds of meeting a person that person 
will make a decision about you based on maybe the colors youre 
wearing your jewelry your hair how youre moving that is what 
image is all about she said thursday at the san franciscobased 
groups third annual meeting 
image is about bringing the best in you so that people 
will listen to what you have to say ms mondejar said 
wearing appropriatecolored clothing is one way executives can 
create an image to achieve their goals she told about two dozen 
executives at a seminar titled corporate savvy 
for example darker colors convey a sense of authority while 
lighter ones indicate friendliness a businessman seeking to 
consummate a deal might want to convey both traits by wearing a 
dark suit with a lightcolored necktie she said 
table manners also can be a winning tool for executives 
according to ms mondejar who said 70 percent of all business 
deals are closed during a meal 
to project a polished professional image executives should 
know the proper way to butter their bread said mj cross an 
image consultant from munster ind 
to butter a bread roll take a bitesized pinch butter that 
bite and put it in your mouth rather than chomping into a large 
piece of buttered bread she advised as the executives prepared to 
launch into a fivecourse demonstration meal at a posh downtown 
restaurant 
otherwise you have a great tendency to leave a buttery 
moustache if you happen to have facial hair ms cross said 
color analysis is another way to assess peoples personalities 
and help businesses succeed ms mondejar said 
the theory groups people into categories based on the four 
seasons depending on the color of their eyes hair and complexion 
an emerging branch of color analysis attaches personality traits to 
each season ms mondejar said in an interview during the 
conference 
for example darkfeatured people are winters while those 
with lighter eyes and complexions are summers she said 
winters tend to be bossy and powerhungry while summers 
are more compromising and harmonious ms mondejar said 
executives can use the theory to assess their competitors and 
also determine what clothing colors can help them project the most 
complimentary professional image she said 
joan c levalley president of a suburban chicago accounting 
firm was among the 150 or so executives who sought 
businessboosting tips at the fourday conference 
ms levalley said she has used a color consultant to improve her 
own appearance and has decorated her office in earth tones to 
project a warm comfortable image for clients 
business are learning that if we dont project ourselves in 
the professional status we are were going to fail because 
somebody else is going to do it better said ms levalley 
</TEXT>
