<TEXT>
isnt that foster grant in bankruptcy court 
the company whose ads asking which star was behind its 
sunglasses produced sales and advertising prominence has sought 
chapter 11 bankruptcy court protection from creditors 
industry executives said foster grant corp foundered in the 
last decade after failing to capitalize on its catchy and 
successful print and television ads of the 1960s and 70s that 
asked isnt that behind those foster grants 
in papers filed thursday in us bankruptcy court in tuscon 
ariz it reported total assets of about 25 million and 
liabilities of about 36 million including nearly 193 million in 
unsecured debt 
foster grant founded in 1919 by sam foster was the first 
company to use abrasionresistant lens coatings that blocked the 
suns ultraviolet rays but is best known for its advertisements 
the first of 17 print ads debuted in 1965 and featured peter 
sellers behind a pair of foster grants other entertainment 
personalities including woody allen vanessa redgrave julie 
christie raquel welch and jane fonda appeared in the ads which 
ran until 1968 
a series of television ads followed and commercials later 
featured nonstars and asked isnt that you behind those foster 
grants 
despite the success of a campaign still remembered today foster 
grants recognizable name never really took them into the high 
level part of the market said mauri edwards foster grants vice 
president of marketing from 196473 
it came through the 70s in pretty good shape but the thing 
went downhill rapidly in the 80s said edwards who now manages 
public relations for the sunglass association of america 
he said foster grant began its downturn after the death in 1971 
of joe foster whose father in 1929 sold a 50 percent interest in 
what was then a small maker of sunglasses and combs to what is now 
goody products 
in 1975 foster grant with more than 300 million in sales of 
petrochemicals sunglasses and other products was sold to the us 
arm of the west german chemicals concern hoechst ag 
it then was acquired by the american unit of the french 
pharmaceutical and chemical company rousseluclaf sa the company 
sold its bulk plastic making operations in the 1970s 
in 1986 foster grant was acquired by andlinger amp co a private 
investment banking and management company 
foster grant vice president ed russell blamed the bankruptcy 
court filing on cash flow problems and low profit margins resulting 
from competition from asian imports 
the company had not been profitable in 1989 nor in the first 
half of 1990 he said adding that loss figures still were being 
compiled 
the company said it sold more than 50 million of sunglasses 
eyeglasses and related lens products in 1989 compared with with 
55 million in 1983 in the same period us retail sales of 
nonprescription sunglasses rose to 17 billion from 885 million 
according to industry figures 
foster grant which had as many as 2000 seasonal employees in 
the 1960s said it was laying off 345 of 475 employees at its main 
distribution center in tucson an assembly plant in nogales 
mexico and a plant in leominster mass for one week starting 
monday 
foster grant still is one of top names in the mass sunglass 
industry where glasses sell for under 10 optiray inc owned by 
goody products of kearny nj is considered the leader in that 
field along with bonneau of dallas 
the market for more expensive sunglasses is led by bausch amp lomb 
inc of rochester ny maker of the rayban line other popular 
brands include the french sunglasses vuarnet and bolle 
foster grants technical products division supplies products to 
the computer automotive sporting goods and electromechanical 
industries 
