been 15525 marks on thursday 
for the week the dollar sank 67 percent against the mark in 
domestic dealings 
in other dealings friday the dollar fell against every major 
currency but the japanese yen in new york trading after falling 
broadly overseas 
the latest decline came despite the governments report of an 
unexpectedly small us trade deficit for june of 507 billion 
despite the improvement dealers said traders shunned the dollar 
because they feel the economy may be headed into a recession and 
that the federal reserve will have no choice but to encourage lower 
interest rates 
when us rates are falling relative to those in other 
countries the dollar is less appealing to foreign investors 
dollar traders are just not interested in the trade picture 
said walter simon a currency options trader at bank julius baer amp 
co they are interested in the whole weakening of the us 
economic climate 
he said the dollar finished above its lows because of some late 
dollarbuying by traders who were reluctant to leave themselves 
exposed over the weekend to the possibility that flareups in the 
persian gulf could push the dollar higher 
the united states seems to be taking a lot more aggressive 
posture toward iraq simon said 
but he said the dollar is demonstrating only limited appeal as a 
haven currency during this international conflict which began with 
iraqs invasion of kuwait on aug 2 
dealers in europe said the dollar was hurt by reported comments 
