<TEXT>
james river corp unveiled a major 
restructuring thursday that includes the sale or shutdown of 13 
billion in specialty operations that have not been profitable 
the announcement was made at the paper companys annual 
shareholders meeting in richmond 
in a statement james river said its restructuring would 
increase the resources available for expansion and allow the 
company to simplify its structure so that it can concentrate on 
global growth opportunities in those james river businesses in 
which it commands a substantial market share which are less 
cyclical and which have the highest potential to provide james 
river with competitive advantage 
the restructuring to be completed within a year will allow 
james river to focus on four core areas towels and tissues dixie 
food service products food and consumer packaging and 
communication papers 
the operations to be divested or closed include business papers 
units in berlingorham and groveton nh and in wiggins miss 
coated printed papers operations in west linn ore and towel and 
tissue operations in south glens falls ny and ashland wis 
the company plans to use cash from operations that are sold to 
reduce debt and repurchase stock the repurchase could involve up 
to 8 million shares depending on market conditions 
the financial flexibility provided by these actions is 
designed to support a major capital investment program to grow the 
companys core businesses the company said 
the operations that are targeted for new spending are in 
alabama louisiana michigan maine oregon washington wisconsin 
and ontario canada 
restructuring charges on firstquarter results are expected to 
reach about 150 million the company said and probably will cause 
a loss for the period 
james rivers stock closed at 2287 thursday on the new york 
stock exchange down 25 cents 
james river based in richmond manufactures pulp paper and 
plastic products sales for the fiscal year ending april 29 were 6 
billion 
