livestock analysts on friday predicted a sharp drop in cattle 
futures prices after a government report showed far more cattle 
were placed on feedlots last month than the market had expected 
the anticipated drop of at least a penny a pound would extend 
losses posted friday on the chicago mercantile exchange ahead of 
