employees in seven new jersey cities and in new york city voted 
in march to dump the union but the election results could be 
tossed out and a new vote ordered if sony loses the case said 
michael lightner an attorney with the labor board 
unfair conduct by an employer might be both unlawful and 
constitute grounds for a new election lightner said its fair 
to say that if we win on the unfair labor practice theyll set 
aside the election 
until the case is resolved the union will remain in power 
the company did not tell union officials why the pictures were 
being taken which prompted the labor board to file the complaint 
lightner said the complaint did not concern the content of the 
video 
neil vander dussen sonys president and chief executive 
officer said the union was told only that sony routinely 
photographs its employees for its own use 
our people just didnt think that it was necessary to go into 
great detail he said they were taking them for the video 
yes but we routinely take pictures of our employees 
vander dussen said the complaint was based on technicalities 
and said that sony employees clearly wanted the union out the vote 
was 7644 against the union 
to make an issue out of this is just to delay the 
decertification process he said 
vander dussan said sony will fight the charges the case must go 
to an administrative law judge if facts in the complaint are 
disputed it then goes to a threemember panel of the labor 
relations board in washington 
an attorney for the local said he would argue that the 
antiunion tone of the video gave employees who watched it a false 
perception of their coworkers and union sentiment 
it creates the impression that the individuals pictured are in 
favor of getting rid of the union said attorney larry cary it 
also creates the impression that the company is watching you and 
we think thats coercive 
a second issue in the complaint filed by the labor board is over 
a 27inch television raffled by sony on the day of the election 
vander dussen said all employees who voted were entered into the 
drawing as a way of ensuring a large turnout and not to induce 
employees to vote against the union as the complaint charges 
if they vote for the union theyre still entered into the 
raffle so i dont see how that makes any sense vander dussen 
said 
