<TEXT>
unleaded gasoline hit a record high friday on 
the new york mercantile exchange friday as crude oil prices shot 
up and speculators kept betting that the middle east standoff would 
curtail supplies 
september wholesale unleaded gas futures soared to as high as 
9625 cents before settling at 9597 cents per gallon up 85 cents 
from thursdays record close 
theyre afraid theres not going to be crude around to make 
gasoline with said ed kevelson a broker with dean witter 
reynolds inc the entire mood is up the whole trend is up 
the september contract for west texas intermediate the 
benchmark us crude finished up 127 at 2863 per barrel 
for the week september crude rose 240 per barrel while 
unleaded gasoline was up 165 cents a gallon 
oil prices have been rising in hectic rumordriven trading 
since iraq invaded neighboring kuwait on aug 2 and major 
industrialized nations responded by embargoing their oil 
the tighter supply combined with the possibility of a broader 
middle east war has spurred waves of buying by speculators hoping 
prices will soar further 
as prices moved up friday there wasnt anything to act as a 
dampener said annlouise hittle a senior oil analyst with 
shearson lehman brothers inc its just a real feeling that this 
situation is going to last for a while 
prices had fallen slightly early in the week as traders 
speculated that diplomats might find a solution to the oil crisis 
but the rally renewed with a vengeance after a meeting thursday 
between president bush and jordans king hussein an ally of iraq 
and the united states produced no progress toward a peaceful 
settlement 
traders were concerned that imports and oil supplies will 
tighten particularly in the northeast which is more dependent on 
foreign oil than other regions hittle said 
gas prices get an added boost because us refining capacity 
already is tight and most foreign gasoline cant be imported 
because it does not meet federal emission standards 
among other energy futures wholesale home heating oil for 
september delivery rose to 8054 cents per gallon up 51 cents for 
the day and 79 cents for the week 
september natural gas rose to 1440 per 1000 cubic feet from 
thursdays 1430 on the week natural gas was down 5 cents 
